==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Myrobolan
<hw>My*rob"o*lan</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>myrobalanum</ets> the
fruit of a palm tree from which a balsam was made, Gr.
<grk>myroba`lanos</grk>; <grk>my`ron</grk> any sweet juice distilling
from plants, any prepared unguent or sweet oil + <grk>ba`lanos</grk> an
acorn or any similar fruit: cf. F. <ets>myrobolan</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
dried astringent fruit much resembling a prune. It contains tannin, and
was formerly used in medicine, but is now chiefly used in tanning and
dyeing. Myrobolans are produced by various species of
<gen>Terminalia</gen> of the East Indies, and of <gen>Spondias</gen> of
South America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myronic</ent>⟦br⟧
